says on the contemporary media landscape, explores ever-changing representations of family life on a global scale. The contributors argue that new recording technologies allows families an unusual kind of freedom-until now unknown-to define and respond to their own lives and memories. Recently released videos made by young émigrés as they discover new homelands and resolve conflicts with their parents, for example, reverberate alongside the dark portrayals of family life in the formal filmmaking of Ang Lee. This book will be a boon to scholars of film theory and media studies, as well as to anyone interested in the construction of the family in a postmodern world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aFamilies. 0aMass media and families. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / General.2bisacsh1 aBaronian, Marie-Aude, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBruin, Joost de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCopier, Laura, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDasgupta, Sudeep, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDijck, José van, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHermes, Joke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKloet, Jeroen de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKooijman, Jaap, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaine, Tarja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeeuw, Sonja de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLord, Catherine M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPisters, Patricia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPisters, Patricia, eeditor.4edt4http: